## ðŸŽ¯ Common Workflows

### Creating a New Package from Scratch

1. **Initialize package structure**:
   ```bash
   mkdir my-package && cd my-package
   tz init
   ```

2. **Add package metadata** to `agents.toml`:
   ```toml
   [package]
   name = "@yourname/my-package"
   version = "1.0.0"
   description = "Your package description"
   license = "MIT"

   [compatibility]
   claude = ">=0.2.0"

   [exports.claude]
   template = "templates/CLAUDE.md.hbs"
   commandsDir = "templates/claude/commands"
   subagentsDir = "templates/claude/agents"
   skillsDir = "templates/claude/skills"
   ```

3. **Create templates directory**:
   ```bash
   mkdir -p templates/claude/{agents,commands,skills}
   ```

4. **Use create-agent skill** to add agents
5. **Use create-skill skill** to add skills
6. **Test locally** with `tz run @yourname/my-package`

---

### Adding Agents to Existing Package

1. Ask Claude: "Use the create-agent skill to create a new code reviewer agent"
2. Claude will use the `create-agent` skill with the appropriate template
3. The new agent will be created in `templates/claude/agents/`
4. Re-run `tz apply` to activate the new agent

---

### Adding Skills to Existing Package

1. Ask Claude: "Use the create-skill skill to create a deployment workflow"
2. Claude will use the `create-skill` skill with the appropriate template
3. The new skill will be created in `templates/claude/skills/`
4. Re-run `tz apply` to activate the new skill

